{
  "text": "With regard to NTG, only one Japanese study observed that lower serum vitamin C levels were correlated with increased risk of NTG [CITATION_1] . The authors speculated that glutamate-stimulated release of vitamin C might decrease oxidative stress induced by glutamate excitotoxicity and reduce the degeneration of retinal ganglion cells [CITATION_2] . The difference between that study and this study is that only vitamin A, B9, C, E and uric acid were investigated using serum samples, and niacin was not included in that study [CITATION_3] .",
  "citation_candidates": [
